metadata.name: Recollection #10
metadata.description:
Recollection | noun
rec·​ol·​lec·​tion

the action or power of recalling to mind

This series, made in the Spring of 2014, is about growing up, becoming an adult, falling in love, or just looking back on hazy distant memories. Almost dream-like.

When the places you're in during a dream are far too perfect and orderly, but at the same time, there's something odd about them that you can't quite figure out.

Perfectly imperfect.

Each photograph will come with a 13x19 print I made myself in 2014.
